			<ns0:name>ncb...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/100032148147647801554/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">NaCl's architecture contains enough threads and communication channels that figuring out which thread should perform a particular task and how to get data to that thread can be a daunting task for anyone not intimately familiar with the system.  For people familiar with the system, any mistakes or misunderstandings could lead to the subtle bugs associated with parallel programming.


The following aspects of NaCl's architecture should be documented:

What threads are there?
What tasks do the threads perform?
When / where / by which other thread is a particular thread created and joined?
Which objects are owned/accessible by which threads?
What assumptions can be made about object lifetimes on each thread?
What communication mechanisms exist between a particular pair of threads?
  Sockets?
  Message queues?
  Thread safe functions?
Which threads can interact with PPAPI, and by what mechanism?</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-15T22:13:28.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-07-28T19:28:44.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Assigned</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
